The paper discusses constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs), which are a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of variable and value elimination is a technique often used in search algorithms for CSPs, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the identification of certain patterns, which is a topic in logic and set theory (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses arc-consistent CSP instances, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
